The paper deals with the problem of sparse phase retrieval, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel algorithm that involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the algorithm in imaging and microscopy, which could place it in cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing). Finally, the paper involves numerical optimization and computational complexity analysis, which could also make it relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
